          POSTDOCTORAL FELLOW / RESEARCH ASSISTANT

The Information Security Research Centre (ISRC) of the Faculty 
of Information Technology is a University Centre and the focus 
of its activities is the control, management and security of
computer systems and networks.  A vacancy exists within the Centre
for a Postdoctoral Fellow or Research Scientist.  The position is
offered for one year.

 The Position:		The person employed in this position will 
			be investigating the application of 
			security protocols and encryption for
			distributed and open systems, determining
			the required algorithms, and designing
			appropriate protocols for the secure and
			efficient usage of these algorithms.

 Qualifications and 	Applicants should have a PhD with a strong
 Skills:		background in data communications/networks,
			information systems security or cryptology;
			extensive programming experience and an 
			interest in applying information security
			techniques to distributed systems.

 Conditions:		Postdoctoral Fellow Salary: $36,285 - $38,950 pa
			Research Scientist Salary: $36,285 - $44,075 pa
			Applicants from outside the Brisbane area may
			be interviewed by telephone.

 Further Information:	A detailed duty statement and selection criteria
			can be obtained from the Personnel Department
			(07) 864 3105.  For further information contact
			Ass Prof Ed Dawson (07) 864 1919, e-mail address
			e.dawson@qut.edu.au.

Closing Date for Applications is June 11th 1993.

Please send applications together with a list of three referees to:

		Personnel Director
		Queensland University of Technology
		GPO Box 2434
		Brisbane  Qld  4001
		Australia.

Quote Job Vacancy Number 200/93




